postcontent: Yugoslavian SKS for sale. For those not familiar with the Yugo version, they were unique in they were fitted with a rifle fired grenade launcher.   Such launchers are obsolete now. I finally just gave up and put my .22 conversion upper on one of them.  The other I'll just sell as it isn't doing me any good with unavailable uppers and no bcg's that aren't priced at their weight in gold.  This lower is made by New Frontier Arms.  It's listed as Multi-Caliber so you can mount whatever you'd like on it (5.56 .223 6.8 .22 etc)  It weighs 1.6 pounds, 7.2oz's lighter than a typical aluminum lower. It has the accu-group composite fire control system installed, but can accommodate your own LPK as well.  The stock is the 6 position adjustable unit.  A lot of people talk down on the polymer AR lowers, but just by looking at how well Glock has done with polymer in their firearms, I think we can all see that these puppies are tough.  I've used my DPMS 5.56 upper on mine and it functions flawlessly.  The first picture shows the lower with a .22LR mag in it.  That mag is not included.
